# Force LF on all text files so the test's line-by-line comparison against
# expected/ output works identically on Windows, macOS, and Linux. Without
# this, a Windows clone with default core.autocrlf=true ends up with CRLF in
# the expected files, and the test fails on every line because of phantom
# carriage returns.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.txt text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
